ABUJA – Senator Sani Musa, one of the contenders for the All Progressives Congress (APC) National Chairmanship position, has been assured that he will be rewarded. He has also been assured that the sacrifice he made for the party will not go in vain. According to the APC National Leader and a presidential aspirant, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, Senator Musa will surely be rewarded by the party following his contributions to the success of APC in 2014/ 2015. Russia Sees Record Virus Cases Second Day Running NGOs Demand Justice For 5yr-Old Pupil Murdered By Proprietor Tinubu gave the assurance when he paid a visit to Senator Musa in Abuja, who just got back from a medical trip. The assurance is coming barely one month to the party National Convention scheduled for February 26, 2022. Tinubu said: “The sacrifices of Distinguished Senator Mohammed Sani Musa for the All Progressives Congress in 2014/2015 will not go in vain, the leadership of the ruling All Progressives Congress are fully aware, Inshallah, he will be rewarded.” Senator Musa, it was noted is a qualified National Chairmanship aspirant with the blueprint for a new vision of the party in a new direction for electoral victory. The lawmaker, who is the Senate Committee Chairman on Senate Services, representing Niger East Senatorial District, explained that Tinubu visited him last night, adding that he came to see how his health is now. POLL “He’s happy to see me feeling very well after returning from this medical trip,” Senator Musa added.